= {{convert|14.18|m|ftin|abbr=on}}\n| Ship decks               = 13\n| Ship deck clearance      = \n| Ship ramps               = \n| Ship ice class           = \n| Ship sail plan           = \n| Ship power               = \n| Ship propulsion          = Diesel-electric: Two shafts: 2 fixed pitch propellers\n| Ship speed               = {{convert|24|kn|lk=in}}\n| Ship capacity            = 3,780 passengers\n| Ship crew                = 1,110\n| Ship notes               = <ref name=vesseltracker>{{cite web | title=Advanced Masterdata for the Vessel ''Costa Favolosa'' | url=http://www.vesseltracker.com/en/Ships/C0sta-Favolosa-9479852.html | work=VesselTracker | year=2011 | accessdate=8 September 2011}}</ref><ref name=\"Cruise Industry News\"/>\n}}\n|}\n\n'''''Costa Favolosa''''' is a cruise ship ordered for [[Costa Crociere]] in October 2007. Based on the {{sclass-|Concordia|cruise ship|0}} design, ''Costa Favolosa'' was laid down by [[Fincantieri]]'s [[Marghera]] shipyard on 5 November 2009 and launched on 6 August 2010. Part of a five-ship expansion of the Costa Crociere fleet, the vessel entered service in July 2011.<ref name=\"fincantieri\">{{cite press release | title=The ''Costa Favolosa'', The Largest Italian Cruise Ship, Entered Service in Venice | url=http://www.fincantieri.it/cms/data/browse/news/000408.aspx | publisher=Fincantieri | date=30 June 2011  | accessdate=10 September 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Design and description==\n[[File:Costa Favolosa ship replica.jpg|thumb|left|Model replica of ''Costa Favolosa'']]\n[[File:Costa Favolosa horn.wav|thumb|left|''Costa Favolosa'' Horn sound.]]\n\nThe vessel is based on the {{sclass-|Concordia|cruise ship|0}} design already in service with Costa Crociere.<ref name=profile>{{cite web |url=http://www.costacruisesasia.com/B2C/AUS/Corporate/The+company/aboutourselves/aboutourselves.htm |title=Company profile |publisher=Costa Cruises |accessdate=16 February 2010}}</ref> At {{GT|114,500}},<ref name=\"fincantieri\" /> she can carry up to 3,800 passengers in 1,506 cabins; six more than previous ''Concordia''-class ships.<ref name=\"Cruise Industry News\"/><ref name=orderPR>{{cite press release |title=Costa Crociere orders two new cruise ships from Fincantieri |publisher=Costa Cruises |date=18 October 2007 |url=http://www.costacruise.com/B2C/USA/Info/two_new_cruise_ship.htm |accessdate=16 February 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140221214403/http://www.costacruise.com/B2C/USA/Info/two_new_cruise_ship.htm |archive-date=21 February 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Construction and career==\n''Costa Favolosa'' and [[sister ship]] {{ship||Costa Fascinosa}} were ordered in October 2007 as part of a [[euro|\u20ac]]2.4 billion expansion of the Costa Crociere fleet, with five ships entering service between 2009 and 2012 to increase the company's passenger capacity by 50%.<ref name=\"Cruise Industry News\">{{cite web |url=http://www.cruiseindustrynews.com/cruise-news/3347-11309-costa-favolosa-and-fascinosa.html |title=''Costa Favolosa'' and ''Fascinosa'' |date=3 November 2009 |accessdate=16 February 2010 |work=Cruise Industry News}}</ref><ref name=Niemela>{{cite news |url=http://www.cruisebusiness.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=932:costa-deliziosa-handed-over&catid=43:latest-news-catecory&Itemid=115 |title=Costa Deliziosa handed over |last=Niemel\u00e4 |first=Teijo |date=31 January 2010 |work=Cruise Business Review |accessdate=16 February 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110708212018/http://www.cruisebusiness.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=932%3Acosta-deliziosa-handed-over&catid=43%3Alatest-news-catecory&Itemid=115 |archivedate=8 July 2011 }}</ref><ref name=profile/> ''Costa Favolosa'' cost [[euro|\u20ac]]510 million to build.<ref name=orderPR/>\n\nThe names of the two ships were selected via competition. The first phase saw 16,000 pairs of names submitted by [[travel agent]]s and their customers from around the world, after being asked to suggest names. These names were to evoke the idea that the ships were magical and glamorous places. 25 name pairs were shortlisted and placed on the company's website, where over 42,000 visitors voted on their favourite. ''Favolosa'' (Italian for \"fabulous\") and ''Fascinosa'' (\"fascinating\" or \"glamorous\") were selected as the winning name pair.<ref name=\"Cruise Industry News\"/>\n[[File:Costa Favolosa Diamanti Bar 1.jpg|thumb|left|''Costa Favolosa'' Diamanti Bar at inside.]]\nThe first section of the cruise ship was [[Keel laying|laid down]] at [[Fincantieri]]'s [[Marghera]] shipyard on 5 November 2009.<ref name=\"Cruise Industry News\"/> The ship was [[Ceremonial ship launching|launched]] from the builder's dry dock on 6 August 2010.<ref name=\"launch\">{{cite web |url=http://www.cruisebusiness.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=1300:costa-favolosa-launched-in-marghera&catid=43:latest-news-catecory&Itemid=115 |title=Costa Favolosa launched in Marghera |date=6 August 2010 |accessdate=7 August 2010 |last=Niemel\u00e4 |first=Teijo |work=Cruise Industry News |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110728084624/http://www.cruisebusiness.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=1300%3Acosta-favolosa-launched-in-marghera&catid=43%3Alatest-news-catecory&Itemid=115 |archivedate=28 July 2011 }}</ref> ''Costa Favolosa'' is the fifteenth ship in service with Costa Crociere.<ref name=\"Cruise Industry News\"/>\n\n===COVID-19 pandemic===\nIn March 2020 during [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]], the ship departed from [[Guadeloupe]]. Six of the disembarked occupants of the ship tested positive for [[COVID-19]].<ref name=foxnews>{{cite web |url=https://www.foxnews.com/travel/2-costa-cruise-ships-toward-florida-sick-crew-members |title=2 Costa cruise ships heading toward Florida with dozens of sick crew members on board |work=Fox News |last=Bartiromo |first=Michael |date=26 March 2020 |access-date=5 April 2020}}</ref> On 26 March, as the ship stopped {{convert|3|mi|spell=in}} offshore from [[Miami]], Florida, the [[United States Coast Guard]] reported the evacuation of seven sick crew members, out of the 1,009 who stayed aboard.<ref name=foxnews/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nbc-2.com/story/41943042/multiple-sick-crew-members-on-costa-magica-costa-favolosa-to-be-evacuated-off-miami |title=Multiple sick crew members on Costa Magica, Costa Favolosa to be evacuated off Miami |work=NBC-2 |last=Massarelli |first=Katelyn |date=26 March 2020 |access-date=5 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/travel/cruises/2020/03/26/coronavirus-costa-magica-costa-favolosa-miami-sick-crew/2914625001/ |title=Two Costa cruise ships to anchor with sick crew in Miami for 'life-critical' care |last=Hines |first=Morgan |work=USA Today |date=26 March 2020 |access-date=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nAn update by CNN on 3 April 2020 stated that the ship was then docked near Miami. Seven crew members and the sick passengers had been evacuated. Other passengers had disembarked in Guadeloupe.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cnn.com/travel/article/cruise-ships-still-sailing/index.html |title=Cruise ships are still scrambling for safe harbor |last=Street |first=Francesca |work=CNN |date=3 April 2020 |access-date=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 April 2020 an Indian crew member died from the disease after the ship was disembarked and was sent into Miami Hospital on 29 March.<ref>[https://www.usatoday.com/story/travel/cruises/2020/04/07/coronavirus-costa-favolosa-crew-member-dies-coral-princess-disembarks/2959938001/ More Coral Princess cruisers leave ship; Costa Favolosa crew member dies of coronavirus] USA Today 7 April 2020</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|IMO 9479852}}\n* [http://www.costacruise.com/usa/costa_favolosa.html Official website]\n\n{{Costa Cruises}}\n{{Concordia class}}\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n\n[[Category:Ships of Costa Cruises]]\n[[Category:Cruise ships]]\n[[Category:2010 ships]]\n[[Category:Cruise ships involved in the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{|{{Infobox ship begin |display title=ital}}\n{{Infobox ship image\n|Ship image=Costa Favolosa 2011-10-18.jpg\n|Ship caption= ''Costa Favolosa''in Piraeus, Athens\n\n}}\n{{Infobox ship career\n| Hide header              = \n| Ship name                = ''Costa Favolosa''\n| Ship renamed             =\n| Ship flag                =\n| Ship owner               = [[Carnival Corporation & plc]]\n| Ship operator            = [[Costa Crociere]]\n| Ship registry            = [[Genoa]], {{flag|Italy|civil}}\n| Ship route               = \n| Ship ordered             = October 2007\n| Ship builder             = [[Fincantieri]], [[Marghera]], [[Venice]]\n| Ship original cost       = [[euro|\u20ac]]510 million\n| Ship yard number         = \n| Ship way number          = \n| Ship laid down           = 5 November 2009\n| Ship launched            = 6 August 2010\n| Ship completed           = \n| Ship christened          = 2 July 2011\n| Ship acquired            = \n| Ship maiden voyage       = 4 July 2011\n| Ship in service          = 4 July 2011\n| Ship out of service      = \n| Ship identification      =* [[Call sign]]: ICPK\n* {{IMO Number|9479852}}\n* {{MMSI|247311100}}\n| Ship fate                = \n| Ship status              = In service\n| Ship notes               = <ref name=vesseltracker/><ref name=\"Cruise Industry News\"/>\n}}\n{{Infobox ship characteristics\n| Hide header              = \n| Header caption           = \n| Ship class               = Modified {{sclass-|Concordia|cruise ship}}\n| Ship type                = \n| Ship tonnage             =*{{GT|113,216}}<!--\n*{{NetT|}}\n*{{DWT|}} -->\n| Ship displacement        = \n| Ship length              = {{convert|290|m|ftin|abbr=on}}\n| Ship beam                = {{convert|40|m|ftin|abbr=on}}\n| Ship height      