se saw 16,000 pairs of names submitted by [[travel agent]]s and their customers from around the world, after being asked to suggest names. These names were to evoke the idea that the ships were magical and glamorous places. 25 name pairs were shortlisted and placed on the company's website, where over 42,000 visitors voted on their favourite. ''Favolosa'' (Italian for \"fabulous\") and ''Fascinosa'' (\"fascinating\" or \"glamorous\") were selected as the winning name pair.<ref name=\"Cruise Industry News\"/>\n[[File:Costa Favolosa Diamanti Bar 1.jpg|thumb|left|''Costa Favolosa'' Diamanti Bar at inside.]]\nThe first section of the cruise ship was [[Keel laying|laid down]] at [[Fincantieri]]'s [[Marghera]] shipyard on 5 November 2009.<ref name=\"Cruise Industry News\"/> The ship was [[Ceremonial ship launching|launched]] from the builder's dry dock on 6 August 2010.<ref name=\"launch\">{{cite web |url=http://www.cruisebusiness.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=1300:costa-favolosa-launched-in-marghera&catid=43:latest-news-catecory&Itemid=115 |title=Costa Favolosa launched in Marghera |date=6 August 2010 |accessdate=7 August 2010 |last=Niemel\u00e4 |first=Teijo |work=Cruise Industry News |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110728084624/http://www.cruisebusiness.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=1300%3Acosta-favolosa-launched-in-marghera&catid=43%3Alatest-news-catecory&Itemid=115 |archivedate=28 July 2011 }}</ref> ''Costa Favolosa'' is the fifteenth ship in service with Costa Crociere.<ref name=\"Cruise Industry News\"/>\n\n===COVID-19 pandemic===\nIn March 2020 during [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]], the ship departed from [[Guadeloupe]]. Six of the disembarked occupants of the ship tested positive for [[COVID-19]].<ref name=foxnews>{{cite web |url=https://www.foxnews.com/travel/2-costa-cruise-ships-toward-florida-sick-crew-members |title=2 Costa cruise ships heading toward Florida with dozens of sick crew members on board |work=Fox News |last=Bartiromo |first=Michael |date=26 March 2020 |access-date=5 April 2020}}</ref> On 26 March, as the ship stopped {{convert|3|mi|spell=in}} offshore from [[Miami]], Florida, the [[United States Coast Guard]] reported the evacuation of seven sick crew members, out of the 1,009 who stayed aboard.<ref name=foxnews/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nbc-2.com/story/41943042/multiple-sick-crew-members-on-costa-magica-costa-favolosa-to-be-evacuated-off-miami |title=Multiple sick crew members on Costa Magica, Costa Favolosa to be evacuated off Miami |work=NBC-2 |last=Massarelli |first=Katelyn |date=26 March 2020 |access-date=5 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/travel/cruises/2020/03/26/coronavirus-costa-magica-costa-favolosa-miami-sick-crew/2914625001/ |title=Two Costa cruise ships to anchor with sick crew in Miami for 'life-critical' care |last=Hines |first=Morgan |work=USA Today |date=26 March 2020 |access-date=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nAn update by CNN on 3 April 2020 stated that the ship was then docked near Miami. Seven crew members and the sick passengers had been evacuated. Other passengers had disembarked in Guadeloupe.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cnn.com/travel/article/cruise-ships-still-sailing/index.html |title=Cruise ships are still scrambling for safe harbor |last=Street |first=Francesca |work=CNN |date=3 April 2020 |access-date=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 April 2020 an Indian crew member died from the disease after the ship was disembarked and was sent into Miami Hospital on 29 March.<ref>[https://www.usatoday.com/story/travel/cruises/2020/04/07/coronavirus-costa-favolosa-crew-member-dies-coral-princess-disembarks/2959938001/ More Coral Princess cruisers leave ship; Costa Favolosa crew member dies of coronavirus] USA Today 7 April 2020</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|IMO 9479852}}\n* [http://www.costacruise.com/usa/costa_favolosa.html Official w