{"title_page": "Seth Porges", "text_new": "{{notability|Biographies|date=September 2014}}\n'''Seth Porges''' is an [[United States|American]] science and technology [[journalist]] and television commentator.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bits.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/06/20/dress-iphone-app/|title=Cloth, a Fashion App, Is Now Weather Sensitive|first=Brian X.|last=Chen|date=20 June 2012|publisher=|accessdate=30 June 2019}}</ref> He appears on numerous television shows on the [[History (U.S. TV network)|History]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WLC4VmRzQS0|title=YouTube|website=www.youtube.com|accessdate=30 June 2019}}</ref> [[National Geographic (U.S. TV channel)|National Geographic]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://channel.nationalgeographic.com/|title=Channel Homepage|website=National Geographic Channel|accessdate=30 June 2019}}</ref> [[Discovery Channel|Discovery]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt2096034/|title=How We Invented the World|publisher=|accessdate=30 June 2019|via=www.imdb.com}}</ref> [[American Heroes Channel|American Heroes]]<ref>http://www.ahctv.com/tv-shows/mafia-vs-kkk/</ref> and [[Travel Channel|Travel]]<ref>http://travelchannel.sndimg.com/shows/worlds-most-extreme/episodes/bridges</ref> channels. Previously, he worked as a senior editor at ''[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]]'' magazine,<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20090731220700/http://www.magazine.org/asme/member_qanda/seth-porges.aspx \"The opportunity to cover pinball in depth is just one reason this guy from DIY heaven (aka \u201cPopular Mechanics\u201d) loves magazines\"], ''[[American Society of Magazine Editors]]'', 29 July 2009. Retrieved 8 November 2018. Archived from [http://www.magazine.org/asme/member_qanda/seth-porges.aspx the original] 31 July 2009.</ref> as an editor at ''[[Popular Mechanics]]'' magazine, as the technology columnist at ''[[Bloomberg News]]''<ref>Porges, Seth. [https://web.archive.org/web/20150924170324/http://www.bloomberg.com/apps/news?pid=newsarchive&sid=aZ4x6c89a4kk \"Livescribe Smartpen Radically Changes Note-Taking: Seth Porges\"], ''[[Bloomberg News]]'', 4 December 2008. Retrieved 8 November 2018. Archived from [https://www.bloomberg.com/apps/news?pid=newsarchive&sid=aZ4x6c89a4kk the original] 24 September 2015.</ref> and as a writer for ''[[TechCrunch]]''.<ref>John Biggs, [https://techcrunch.com/2011/12/16/getcloth-lets-you-store-your-outfits-in-your-phone/ \"Cloth Lets You Store Your \u201cOutfits\u201d In Your \u201cPhone\u201d\"], ''Techcrunch'', 16 December 2011</ref> He lives in Brooklyn, New York, and is a graduate of [[Northwestern University]]\u2019s [[Medill School of Journalism]]''.\n\nPorges has appeared as a guest commentator on television networks such as [[MSNBC]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.msn.com/|title=MSN - Outlook, Office, Skype, Bing, Breaking News, and Latest Videos|website=www.msn.com|accessdate=30 June 2019}}</ref> [[Fox News]],<ref>[http://video.foxnews.com/v/3955846/fire-starter \"Fire Starter - Fox News Video\"], ''Fox News''</ref> [[G4 (U.S. TV channel)|G4]], [[Fox Business]] and [[CNBC]], as well as the web shows ''TechVi''<ref>[http://techvi.com/tag/guest-seth-porges/ \"Guest: Seth Porges\"], ''TechVi''</ref> and ''[[Rocketboom]]''.<ref>[http://www.rocketboom.com/pop-mech/ \"Popular Mechanics Breakthrough Awards 2010\"], ''Rocketboom''</ref> His writing has appeared in publications such as ''[[BusinessWeek]]'', ''[[Men\u2019s Health]]'', ''[[Men\u2019s Journal]]'' and ''[[Editor & Publisher]]''.<ref>http://sethporges.com/</ref> In 2014, he produced a documentary<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mashable.com/2013/08/28/action-park/|title=Inside the World's Most Dangerous Amusement Park|first=Seth|last=Porges|website=Mashable|accessdate=30 June 2019}}</ref> about [[Action Park]] that went viral and is credited with inspiring the park to change its name.<ref>Tim Donnelly, [https://nypost.com/2014/06/28/the-return-of-the-worlds-most-dangerous-theme-park/ \"The dangerous return of the world\u2019s most insane theme park\"], ''New York Post'', 28 June 2014</ref>\n\nIn 2012 Porges co-founded Cloth<ref>{{cite news |last1=Shatzman |first1=Celia |title=The New Cloth App Makes Your Virtual Closet Dreams Come True |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/celiashatzman/2014/11/11/the-new-cloth-app-makes-your-virtual-closet-dreams-come-true/#44b0ac7d75ff |accessdate=17 April 2020 |publisher=Forbes}}</ref>, a fashion app with designer [[Wray Serna]]. A unique profiling system developed by Cloth gives retailers a better sense of who their customers are and what is in their closets, allowing them to better target and engage their customers.\n\nHe is the son of the neuroscientists [[Stephen Porges]] and [[C. Sue Carter]], and is the subject of a song by the musician [[Wesley Willis]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/Wesley-Willis-And-The-Dragnews-Joe-Hunter/release/740878|title=Wesley Willis And The Dragnews - Joe Hunter|website=Discogs|accessdate=30 June 2019}}</ref> In 2009, he received attention as a test pilot on the maiden voyage of an experimental pulse jet-powered carousel.<ref>Danny Allen, [https://gizmodo.com/5369993/jet+powered-carousel-makes-fiery-maiden-voyage \"Video: Jet-Powered Carousel Makes Fiery Maiden Voyage\"], ''Gizmodo.com'', 29 September 2009</ref> In 2006, he appeared as a contestant on ''[[Cash Cab (American game show)|Cash Cab]]''. In 2011, he led a [[Twitter]] campaign that succeeded in causing [[Chipotle]] to list the presence of bacon in its pinto beans.<ref>[http://consumerist.com/2011/08/tweets-get-chipotle-to-change-menus-to-show-pinto-beans-cooked-with-bacon.html \"Tweets Get Chipotle To Change Menus To Show Pinto Beans Cooked With Bacon\"], ''The Consumerist'', August 2011</ref> That same year, he was named as one of \"50 Media Power Bachelors\" by ''The New York Observer''.<ref>[http://www.observer.com/2011/08/the-free-agent-list-2011s-50-media-power-bachelors/#slide24 \"The Free Agent List: 2011\u2032s 50 Media Power Bachelors\"], ''The New York Observer'', 15 August 2011</ref> and one of ''Stylecaster'''s \"Top 25 IT Kids of 2011\".<ref>[http://www.stylecaster.com/lifestyle/17698/stylecasters-top-25-it-kids-2011#153184 \"StyleCaster's Top 25 IT Kids of 2011\"], ''StyleCaster''</ref> He is an expert on the history of [[pinball]].<ref>[http://www.rocketboom.com/history-of-pinball/ \"The History of Pinball\"], ''Rocketboom''</ref>{{dead link|date=June 2019}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|sethporges.com}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Porges, Seth}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American television personalities]]\n[[Category:American technology writers]]\n[[Category:American science writers]]\n[[Category:American magazine editors]]\n[[Category:Medill School of Journalism alumni]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "{{notability|Biographies|date=September 2014}}\n'''Seth Porges''' is an [[United States|American]] science and technology [[journalist]] and television commentator.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bits.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/06/20/dress-iphone-app/|title=Cloth, a Fashion App, Is Now Weather Sensitive|first=Brian X.|last=Chen|date=20 June 2012|publisher=|accessdate=30 June 2019}}</ref> He appears on numerous television shows on the [[History (U.S. TV network)|History]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WLC4VmRzQS0|title=YouTube|website=www.youtube.com|accessdate=30 June 2019}}</ref> [[National Geographic (U.S. TV channel)|National Geographic]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://channel.nationalgeographic.com/|title=Channel Homepage|website=National Geographic Channel|accessdate=30 June 2019}}</ref> [[Discovery Channel|Discovery]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt2096034/|title=How We Invented the World|publisher=|accessdate=30 June 2019|via=www.imdb.com}}</ref> [[American Heroes Channel|American Heroes]]<ref>http://www.ahctv.com/tv-shows/mafia-vs-kkk/</ref> and [[Travel Channel|Travel]]<ref>http://travelchannel.sndimg.com/shows/worlds-most-extreme/episodes/bridges</ref> channels. Previously, he worked as a senior editor at ''[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]]'' magazine,<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20090731220700/http://www.magazine.org/asme/member_qanda/seth-porges.aspx \"The opportunity to cover pinball in depth is just one reason this guy from DIY heaven (aka \u201cPopular Mechanics\u201d) loves magazines\"], ''[[American Society of Magazine Editors]]'', 29 July 2009. Retrieved 8 November 2018. Archived from [http://www.magazine.org/asme/member_qanda/seth-porges.aspx the original] 31 July 2009.</ref> as an editor at ''[[Popular Mechanics]]'' magazine, as the technology columnist at ''[[Bloomberg News]]''<ref>Porges, Seth. [https://web.archive.org/web/20150924170324/http://www.bloomberg.com/apps/news?pid=newsarchive&sid=aZ4x6c89a4kk \"Livescribe Smartpen Radically Changes Note-Taking: Seth Porges\"], ''[[Bloomberg News]]'', 4 December 2008. Retrieved 8 November 2018. Archived from [https://www.bloomberg.com/apps/news?pid=newsarchive&sid=aZ4x6c89a4kk the original] 24 September 2015.</ref> and as a writer for ''[[TechCrunch]]''.<ref>John Biggs, [https://techcrunch.com/2011/12/16/getcloth-lets-you-store-your-outfits-in-your-phone/ \"Cloth Lets You Store Your \u201cOutfits\u201d In Your \u201cPhone\u201d\"], ''Techcrunch'', 16 December 2011</ref> He currently{{when|date=November 2018}} lives in Brooklyn, New York, and is a graduate of [[Northwestern University]]\u2019s [[Medill School of Journalism]]''.\n\nPorges has appeared as a guest commentator on television networks such as [[MSNBC]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.msn.com/|title=MSN - Outlook, Office, Skype, Bing, Breaking News, and Latest Videos|website=www.msn.com|accessdate=30 June 2019}}</ref> [[Fox News]],<ref>[http://video.foxnews.com/v/3955846/fire-starter \"Fire Starter - Fox News Video\"], ''Fox News''</ref> [[G4 (U.S. TV channel)|G4]], [[Fox